SUMMARY
    Output a string repeatedly until terminated.

SYNOPSIS
    "yes" *word

DESCRIPTION
    Outputs the specified sentence, or "y" if no parameters specified, until
    the program is terminated.

OPTIONS
    N/A.

EXIT CODES
    The Nutbox-wide exit codes adhered to by all Nutbox commands are:

        0 - success; the program successfully ran to completion.
        1 - failure; the program encountered an error while executing.
        2 - failure; the program was asked to display its help text.

EXAMPLES
    yes
    Outputs the string "y" to the console until terminated by Ctrl-C.

    yes foo
    Outputs the string "foo" to the console until terminated by Ctrl-C.

TIPS
    N/A

BUGS
    1. The 'yes' command itself: Probably the most lame command in existence.

